    Let hir be proc translate_to_hir from ToHIR with ast
    Let java_code be proc generate_java_code from FromHIR with hir

    Let _java_ok be java_code is not equal to 0
    proc test_assert with _java_ok, "Generated Java code should not be null"

    Display "PASS: Round-trip interface test"
    Display ""

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Test Runner
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Test driver: prints a header, then invokes each test_* procedure in source
order grouped by lexer, parser, Java->HIR, HIR->Java, and round-trip
sections. Always returns 1 since individual tests print their own
PASS/FAIL lines — the runner aggregates by line scanning rather than
return-code summing.
@End Reasoning
